headline: Oracle Catches a Downgrade. New Bear Sees ‘Daunting’ Cloud Computing Landscape.
summary: FEATURE   Oracle stock caught a downgrade Friday from a new bear who argued that the “hype” surrounding the company wouldn’t be enough to offset intense competition. Monness, Crespi, Hardt & Co. analyst Brian White downgraded Oracle to Sell from Neutral and set a price target of $130.

headline: Oracle stock slides as analyst cuts to sell
summary: Investing.com -- Oracle shares came under pressure premarket Friday, down around 1.3% after Monness, Crespi, Hardt downgraded the stock to Sell from Neutral and set a 12-month price target of $130, below its current price of $168.79.
